seed_chunks:
Rain-slicked and fluorescent-bleached, the city runs on three polite masks. **St. Brigid Morgue Services** swears it’s modernizing deathcare; behind the chilled doors it reroutes bodies, edits tags, and sells second lives to the highest bidder. **The Halcyon Benevolent Trust** bankrolls clinics and soup lines; in private it funds “continuity” trials—harvesting organs, identities, and silence—using the morgue as its valve. **The Lanternmen** look like union muscle for docks and sanitation; secretly they’re the couriers, moving sealed gurneys and forged paperwork through service tunnels. Halcyon pays, St. Brigid supplies, Lanternmen deliver—until missing relatives, rival crews, and Silas’s questions turn their shared pipeline into a knife fight.

```json
{
  "factions": [
    {
      "name": "St. Brigid Morgue Services",
      "public_front": "A reputable municipal contractor modernizing morgue operations and deathcare logistics.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Alters toe-tags and intake records to launder bodies and identities through the city system for profit and leverage."
    },
    {
      "name": "The Halcyon Benevolent Trust",
      "public_front": "A philanthropic foundation funding clinics, shelters, and public health initiatives.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Finances covert 'continuity' programs—organ harvesting, identity recycling, and hush payments—using morgue access to source and erase."
    },
    {
      "name": "The Lanternmen",
      "public_front": "A hard-nosed labor outfit providing dock, sanitation, and security manpower.",
      "hidden_agenda": "Runs the transport network for illicit cargo: bodies, paperwork, and bribes moved through tunnels and service corridors."
    }
  ]
}
```

Rain hammers the loading bays at St. Brigid as an internal audit team arrives early—too early—forcing night supervisor **Mara Keene** to rush a “routine transfer” before daylight and before paper trails harden. A Lanternmen convoy idles in the service alley, engines muttering, while **Doc Vellum** (Halcyon’s fixer) leans on Keene to move one particular gurney tagged with Silas’s unforgotten name. Across town, Halcyon’s free clinic suffers a sudden “power failure,” scrambling records and trapping patients—cover for a continuity trial pickup that could turn into a riot if the doors stay locked.

```json
{
  "events": [
    {
      "name": "St. Brigid Surprise Audit & Midnight Transfer",
      "description": "A municipal audit team arrives at St. Brigid ahead of schedule, forcing night supervisor Mara Keene to fast-track a sensitive body transfer before intake logs can be compared. A Lanternmen convoy waits in the alley while Halcyon fixer Doc Vellum pressures Keene to move a gurney carrying the first falsified identity—Silas’s anchor case—out through service tunnels.",
      "tensions": [
        "Audit staff could discover altered tags and missing chain-of-custody signatures",
        "Lanternmen may use intimidation or violence if the transfer stalls",
        "Keene risks becoming the scapegoat if Halcyon needs someone to burn"
      ]
    },
    {
      "name": "Halcyon Clinic Blackout & Continuity Pickup",
      "description": "Halcyon’s flagship free clinic reports an abrupt power failure that wipes terminals and locks down exits. The blackout masks a continuity-trial extraction: patients are rerouted, one is quietly sedated, and a courier team prepares a sealed transport order routed through St. Brigid. If staff or families realize the lockdown isn’t for safety, panic could spike into a street-level riot.",
      "tensions": [
        "Patients and families may force exits, drawing police and media attention",
        "Clinic staff could leak evidence of the extraction if they regain system access",
        "A rushed pickup increases the chance of mislabeling, leaving a trace Silas can follow"
      ]
    }
  ]
}
```

